  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 .\u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0b95\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc8 \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0baf\u0b95\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bcb\u0ba4 \u0bb5\u0bb4\u0bbf\u0bae\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0baa\u0baf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bc8 \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0baf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Party groups that use violent anti-democratic means to seize power .government buildings may be banned - government official",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "Any group, political party or organization that adopts violent anti-democratic methods to seize power or capture government buildings may be banned, a Ceresta government official said.",
        "The ban is being seriously investigated as it has been reported that some groups are planning to protest against the government again on the 9th.",
        "A government official has said that attempts to occupy and damage government buildings to capture them will be considered acts of terrorism.",
        "The Ministry of Public Security has sought legal advice on the possibility of banning a party or group or organization indulging in such activities.",
        "\"We are looking into tougher measures but this will not affect the peaceful protests,\" an official said.",
        "A state of emergency is now in place following Parliament's approval this week and will last until the 18th.",
        "The information about the ban has been released while the authorities are engaged in arresting those involved in the violence from July 9 to 13.",
        "In the coming days, the authorities will release the details of 40 people involved in violence, damage to property, thefts, etc. in the houses of Udiyogapur and seek the public's cooperation in arresting them.",
        "Investigations are underway into 300 people who breached the security barriers of President Ranil Wickremesinghe's official residence and entered the area."
      ],
